HIV/AIDS: Sabbin cututtuka sun karu da kashi 14 cikin 100 a kasar Sin
Kasar Sin ta ce yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS ya karu da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Jami'an lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 8,20,000 ne ke fama da cutar a kasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na shekarar 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane 40,000.
Yawancin mutanen da ke cikin sabon yanayin sun kamu da cutar ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ke nuna canji a baya.
A wasu yankunan ƙasar Sin, cutar HIV tana yaduwa sosai ta wurin ba da jini mai ƙazanta.
Amma a taron da aka yi a lardin Yunnan, jami'an lafiya na kasar Sin sun ce, wannan ya rage yawan mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV zuwa kusan sifili.
Duk da haka, adadin mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS a kasar Sin ya karu da mutane 100,000 a kowace shekara.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce ga al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
Tun daga shekarar 1997 a kasar Sin, ba laifi ba ne a yi jima'i tsakanin mutane, amma bambancin ra'ayi game da LGBT ya karu a ko'ina.
Binciken ya nuna cewa, a sakamakon ka'idodin da kasar ta saba da su, kimanin kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza suna yin aure da mata.
Rashin kariya daga irin wannan dangantaka ne ke haifar da yawancin cututtukan.
Tun daga shekara ta 2003, a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin magance matsalar, gwamnatin Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da magungunan HIV a duniya.
